  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House", 
    "date": "2020-07-27T04:00:00Z", 
    "text": "Promotion Accessibility Act\n\nThis bill authorizes members of the Foreign Service or the Senior Foreign Service to submit a gap memo in advance of having their performance evaluated by a selection board, and it prohibits members of a selection board from considering such a submission as negative when evaluating a member's performance.\n\nA gap memo is a written record indicating and explaining a gap in the record of a member that is due to personal circumstances, including for health, family, or other reasons."
  }, 
